GhanaLSS: Partially registered
================================

Working (registered in dvc.yaml)
---------------------------------
- cluster_features — all 7 waves via API
- household_roster — all 7 waves via API

Bug fixes applied
-----------------
- Fixed imports: scripts imported "from ghana import ..." but utility
  module is ghanalss.py. Updated all imports to "from ghanalss import ..."
- Fixed Makefile generic rule: referenced malawi.py (copy-paste error),
  now references ghanalss.py
- Fixed case-sensitivity in mapping.py: GHANALSS -> GhanaLSS in
  waves 1988-89, 1991-92, 1998-99

Not yet registered (need Make backend + dependency fixes)
---------------------------------------------------------
- food_acquired — wave-level .py scripts exist for all 7 waves, but
  Make depends on other_features.parquet via Makefile chain
- other_features — country-level aggregator exists but no wave-level
  scripts to produce wave parquets
- household_characteristics — country-level aggregator exists but no
  wave-level scripts
- food_expenditures, food_prices, food_quantities — produced by
  food_prices_quantities_and_expenditures.py from food_acquired

Next steps
----------
1. Create wave-level other_features.py for each wave (extracts region/
   rural from the same data_info.yml sources used by cluster_features)
2. Once other_features works, food_acquired Make chain should unblock
3. Then household_characteristics and food_prices/quantities/expenditures
   follow
